Assignment 1 Part 2: Restaurant Finder

--------------
Included Files
--------------
    * a1part1.cpp
    * lcd_image.cpp
    * yeg_rest_coords.cpp
    * Makefile
    * README
    * include/
        * a1part1.h
        * lcd_image.h
        * yeg_rest_coords.h

-----------
Accessories
-----------
    * Arduino Mega 2560 Board X1
    * USB cable type A/B X1
    * 3.5" TFT LCD 480x320 HD color screen module for Arduino UNO & MEGA 2560
        board with touch panel X1
    * Dual axis XY Joystick with push switch for Arduino X1
    * Breadboard X1
    * Male jumper wire X7
    * Male-to-female jumper wire X5

--------------------
Wiring Instructions
--------------------
    * Arduino Analog Pin A8 <--> BB <--> Joystick VRy
    * Arduino Analog Pin A9 <--> BB <--> Joystick VRx
    * Arduino Digital pin 53 <--> BB <--> Joystick Pin SW
    * Arduino GND <--> BB GND <--> BB GND <--> Joystick GND
    * Arduino +5V Pin <--> BB +5V <--> BB +5V <--> Joystick +5V

---------------------
Running Instructions
---------------------
    1. Connect the Arduino with the appropriate componenets (ex: TFT display) to
    a computer using an A-B style USB cable. Ensure that the Arduino is using
    the proper serial port (/dev/ttyACMO0).

    2. In the directory containing the files a1part1.cpp and Makefile, use
    the command "make upload" to upload the code to the Arduino.

-----
Notes
-----
    * a1part1.cpp contains the main program.
    * a1part1.h declares necessary Arduino pins, constants (ex: TFT screen
        dimensions), structs, function prototypes, template code for swapping
        two items in an array, and documentation.
    * lcd_image.h declares the lcd_image_draw() function, which draws an image
        from SD card memory onto the TFT display.
    * lcd_image.cpp contains the implementation of the lcd_image_draw()
        function.
